caption: Definitely a spot worth visiting, the food is great and fresh, the rates are affordable and it is always well organized here. Kudos.

Such friendly staff and DELICIOUS food!!!! Can't wait to eat here again!
Delicious beef tenderloin ..  I didn’t like the Mac and cheese ..  Great service ..
Great food and great service. I definitely will be recomending this place

Downtown tapas style restaurant. We had two kinds of empanadas, the ceviche, the lamb shank, a rice pilaf, a mushroom dish and several others. The pieces of fish and shrimp in the ceviche were larger than I was accustomed to, but the marinade was citrusy, fresh and fragrant. My favourite was the lamb shank.
Great tasting food at decent prices...
We came with a big group and they were super welcoming. I had the best ribs there in a long time. The empanadas were out of this world. You should DEFINITELY eat here!
Fantastic food, awesome service, and the owner is there, cooking and cares deeply!
Great spot for Spanish seafood
Ceviche trio was lovely, everything was great, service delightful!

I covered for a group of 6 and someone tried to sneak in an extra 20% tip on top of the automatic party size gratuity.  Food was a nice pan latin theme and service was good, but seeing the charge 2 days later left a bitter taste even though I have a copy of the receipt for a credit dispute on the difference.
Great flavorfully food
Best checken in town

First time here while on a business trip. I was seated quickly, staff was friendly and checked up on me frequently. The items on the menu were a bit pricey, so I opted just to get a chicken salad sandwich. I had no idea this was going to be …

Great Latin America food family ambient easy parking on curb side on Pine St.

The chicken here is so good - I think it's meant to be the same style as the famous one from Zuni Cafe. I typically will get that for lunch, which comes with bread salad (the best) and a side of choice. Other good entrees include the …

My preferred spot for latin american food. The service here is outstanding.
Great food and service, definitely worth trying.  Empanadas and roasted chicken are delicious.
latin american food at this place - delicious. Everyone at our table was quite pleased. I look forward to a return visit.
My top spot for quality latin american food. A preferred evening place. I'll return with my coworkers. The bill was fair for the quality of the food.

Semi-Peruvian restaurant with good food and very friendly staff. Ceviche was good and my group split a whole rotisserie chicken.  If you’re expecting lots of seafood dishes, you’ll probably be disappointed.
Great food and Atmosphere
Amazing fusion chipotle SEAFOOD pot pie. Super tender Lomo Saltado Inviting and family friendly.
Expecting Cuban cuisine, turned out to be a Peruvian Fusion cuisine. Probably good in Peruvian, will try some other day.
A real treat.  Open for dinner in the financial district with delicious food and great service!!

Not bad, but not great. Empanadas were poor compared to other Latin places in SF. Had the ceviche mix platter and 2 of the 3 were quite good but the tuna one didn’t taste that fresh. Chicken and lomo saltado were pretty average. Dunno if it’s worth a revisit.
Cevechi was fantastic.

We were so happy to have discovered La Fusion during our stay in San Francisco. A welcoming and relaxing place for lunch. Both dishes were so delicious and moreish (so were the dipping sauces)! The staff were friendly and efficient. Highly recommended!
The food was great, nice size portions, very nice atmosphere and a great service. We eat 5 days a week in financial district  they are definitely the best so far and I’m happy to recommend  them.
The service is great and the food it better!

(Translated by Google) Although the price of the dishes is a little high for the portions, each dish is unique, delicious and full of taste. The service is friendly and fast. The place clean and friendly.  (Original) Bien que le prix des …
Excellent food & friendly service

Came here for a quick lunch and really enjoyed the atmosphere. We beat the crowd and out waiter was the friendliest man and was really great at explaining the dishes and some of his favorite options. We ordered a ton of ceviche and it was …

I'm usually easy to impress, but I didn't got wowed by la fusión. Overpriced small portions; with much less flavor than I expected. Tried lamb chank and lomo saltado; overall the Mac&cheese was tastier than those two. Disappointed.
The food was great !
Excellent - had the seafood pot pie.
It's a bit on the pricier side but the food and beer was definitely worth it, I ordered the chicken sandwich and it's the best one I've had here in the USA, I would recommend it
Good food friendly staff
Delicious food, only thing is I felt that food was slow to get out.

So glad we came here for a late lunch.  We were absolutely famished when we arrived, probably ordered too much food and completely stuffed ourselves, and the food was so good that we finished everything and there wasn't a single bad dish. …
Very good restaurant supply the food of Latin American, Good and good service
A little pricey but clean, relatively healthy options. Fried chicken and ceviche.
The food here is excellent. The Cesar salad was the best I’ve had in years—they even serve it with anchovies. The white bean casoulette is great.
Overpriced rotisserie chicken thats simply salted.. no herbs, no flavorful brine. Just plain boring salted rotisserie chicken and forgettable sides.

Prices sort of high, it's a very small and loud place, food was just okay. To drink I ordered the Chicha Morada which was good and for entrée I ordered the 1/4 chicken and the cilantro rice as a side dish, but sadly the chicken tasted …
Great food friendly service.
Place was ok, and so was the food. Very very homie menu. Nothing remarkable, although Arroz con Pollo was good. Super clean and friendly staff. The don’t serve cocktails, just beer, sangria and wine.
Delicious inspired food, chef was amazingly attentive to our 4yo, can't recommend enough.

(Translated by Google) Great service, delicious food  ! If you come to San Francisco do not miss the opportunity to get to this restaurant, Love all the food, the service is the best and the dessert is amazing, The owner of the restaurant …
Nice place good food, the plates were a bit small
It was a cold day and the asparagus soup was perfect for the occasion. Rest of the meal was also very good

Great restaurant! Amazing staff and family run. The food was awesome, it was obvious the food was prepared with care to both authenticity and quality. You could taste how fresh everything was. We had a three course meal. The empanadas were …
Loved it delicious food and great service .
One of my favorite restaurants. Seafood pot pie is THE BEST. Also great ceviche and chicken.
Excellent food.   Couldn't be better.
Authentic Latin food, delicious and worth it. Service was friendly, atmosphere was perfect for a cozy dinner after a long day at a conference.  A gem of a find in the neighborhood.
Very good food, loved the sweet empanadad! But the sangria had too much cloves, was a bit like iced cold mulled wine.
Unique flavors. Don't miss the rotisserie chicken and  pot pie.
Amazing find. Very healthy and tasty food. We were staying near the mall and are there everyday. Recommend to everyone.
Great food and great people, love this place for a quick lunch or dinner.

Compact menu with some great choices. Some of the best empanadas I've had anywhere. Try the desert empanada. Eddy knocks it out with this one. The service is wonderful. The flavors are terrific. The portions are large. At 6'2" and 280#, I don't do "small plates". I was a happy camper. I WILL be back, Eddy & Jennifer! Count on it!
Ceviche good ..  rest of food OK.
Food was good, but very pricey. Small restaurant.
Pretty pricy, one of those fancy type places where you pay more for smaller dishes. The pork dishes and mac and cheese were good. The sweet potato fries were just okay.
Everything was excellent, special shout out for the tuna tartar!!
Limited menu, kinda pricey, but really good food and service. Empanadas and lomo were great!
Everything went above and beyond expectations. It's in a oddly quiet part of fidi, but should not be overlooked.

After coming here several times I have to say it's becoming a favorite spot of mine! The staff is friendly, and their food is great! All of their small plates and entrees are incredibly flavorful. Prices are moderate ($15-30) for entrees, but I haven't been disappointed a single time coming here. Will be visiting again soon.
Best cebiche ever
Food was tasty, but rather greasy for my taste. Cannot fault the restaurant for this, but  was expecting something healthier. Otherwise, a nice and clean place with decent service.
Great service, good food. Reasonably priced for SF. Nicely presented.
The best rotisserie chicken I've ever had. Save a little room for the flourless chocolate torte!
I love their Yucca fries and sauces, meats, and vegetables! The atmosphere and service is exceptional.
I travel a lot for work all over the world. This place tanks in my top 5 meals of the last 6 years. I had the amazing Lamb Shank. Next time, I hope to try the stew.

Excellent food and service!
Great food. Great service.
Small but intimate place. Latin inspired food.
I had the seafood potbelly which was better than I had expected, and the truffle Mac & Cheese which was underwhelming. I wasn't very in pressed with the place or the service.
Amazing food!
The dishes are very tasty, great size and beautiful presentation. It's a fusion of good food and excellent customer service. The best complement the tres leches dessert!
Was very tasty! Really really tasty indeed!!
Absolutely fantastic!!!! From appetizers to desserts.....no jokeing!
Visited for lunch the first time - terrific food and really good service in a small, comfy space.
Good Peruvian food! The rotisserie chicken was great!

We were looking for a ceviche place close to our hotel and ended up here. It’s been almost a year since we were there but I still think about how good that ceviche was! My friend ordered the roast chicken and caesar salad and said it was …

Such a gem is this place! The “Seared Yellowfin Ban Mi” is just superb! The “Super Spring Rolls” are so yum! They are also starting “Steal Spring Rolls” - got to taste it today, just delicious!! They have a patio seating as well and Tina is such a great host. Had a very good experience!

(Translated by Google) A delicious and cheap place, a very fresh dish, is a fusion of Asian and Mediterranean and Mexican cuisine. Sangria has a big pot, so delicious~  (Original) 好吃又便宜的地方，很新颖的菜色，是亚洲风味和地中海、墨西哥菜的大融合。Sangria一上一大壶，好喝~
The lamb shank is amazing!
Grabbed some quick take out from La Fusion. Flavours of the tuna and mixed seafood cheviches were amazing. Really fresh tasting ingredients with great taste combinations.

Great place to have a small dinner with a friend, between Market & Chinatown. The food was limited to a select menu they have obviously mastered. I would recommend this to anyone looking for a cozy dinner with a friend. PS they also have a very good selection of beers, not just the local varieties.
Delicious food. The portions seem small and overpriced but that is standard San Francisco especially in the downtown FiDi area. Delicious juices too if you are not drinking alcohol.
My friend proclaimed “this is the best pork chop I’ve ever eaten”. You can’t go wrong here, very tasty.
Fantastic restaurant! Great service, simple menu, and not bad wine selection.
Excellent food
Good lunch. Good wine. Felt like I wasn’t in SF anymore. (I could use a vacation.) I had the seafood pot pie. Delicious. Service was excellent. I look forward to dining there again.
Unique
Loooooooved it!
Awesome ceviche!
The food is excellent, the service is also excellent.

Love the food. Its always good. I prefer to go for a mid to late lunch. Good wine list. The warm bread salad is super super yummy and the chicken is always perfect. Start your meal with a ceviche and you'll roll yourself out the door happy.
Excellent service: Friendly, fast. Food was great.
Food was delicious! I highly recommend this place.

The place is very welcoming with a kind and knowledgeable servers/staff. I got the Seafood pot pie and truffle mac & cheese to accompany. The Mac & Cheese itself is a bit generic, nothing new here, but when combined with the Chipotle gravy from the pot pie, the combination was a masterpiece.

Small hole-in-the-wall place with amazing food! We were a party of 14 and was able to get a table in the back. The sangria is delicious - it will not disappoint, the chicken is what they are known for.  My husband had a half chicken and …
Great food and service
Nice cozy restaurant. Ordered the half chicken, really delicious.

Loved the cuisine and service. It took no time for the server to bring our starters. The dishes were just the right temperature. The ambience and crowd was trendy. The rates are are a little high, but worth the food quality and taste. The …
friendly staff
Amazing food!! Discovery of new taste!
Great tasty plates, perfect service. Portions seem small but are actually good enough. We randomly got there without any expectation, and left totally charmed. We'll come back...
Good tuna, ceviche, and pretty decent sangria!

Was recommended this place by a local friend, it was the closest to us after flying in from London with major jetlagcand three kids and we loved it. Very small, super fast and friendly service. Special fries and tried chicken both amazing, ceviche very good.
I'm not a fan but the gf loves it. Mashed potatoes are watery.... Sauces they give are bland.... Yea, I'm just not a fan at all.
July 2015: Lovely place to dine . We have our lunch, food are tasty and delicious, first try on this Latin America food. Fast service.
Had the Seafood Pot Pie, it was amazing! Fast service and friendly staff.
I love the food and staff. Always make me feel at home here! Best ceviche!

I've only been here a couple times but it's never disappointed. The seafood pot pie was really delicious. The specialty fries are also a good pick, though on the expensive side for the small portion. Beer and sangria available.
Great food and close to Pagan Idol!!!
I got the lamb shank. It was delicious. The meat literally falls right off the bone. So juicy and tender.
Perfect food.  Friendly and cool atmosphere.
Tuna tartar , lamb shank
Good food and very nice owner

Excellent service, good sangria, and absolutely delicious food. The seafood pot pie has been my favorite since I first set foot in this restaurant. Also really like the ceviche, empanadas, and yuca fries. Only downside is this place is small and can get crowded so plan accordingly.
Pretty small space but cozy and elegant decors. Staffs were pretty helpful and attentive. The food is excellent! Price tag is not in the cheap range but completely worth every penny.
Great ceviche! Really really friendly bartender. We told her we were moving to San Francisco and she gave us advice on where to live.

Delicious food

Fusion.
Had the mushroom dish, exceeded my expectations, was so good!
Delicious. The chicken is really good, but get at least a half per person. Seafood pot pie is spectacular. Civiche is good. Sangria is okay, bit sweet but some people like that.
Very good Latin American-style food; a bit pricey for lunch, but a nice change of pace in the FiDi
Delicious food! Seafood put is amazing
Amazing rotisserie chicken
Chicken was very well done. We liked everything we tried.. yucca fries, ceviche, sangria! I would definitely go again

Oh my gosh! The most amazing ceviche EVER!   So fresh. The most beautiful delicate balance of flavors and meticulous choice of fish.  You cannot be disappointed, only enamored with the chef's ability to create nirvana for your palate.

Tiny, cozy spot for some interesting Latin (mostly Peruvian) food. They've got some more straightforward staples like empanadas, roasted chicken, and sangria. But La Fusion also offers some items a little off the beaten path like a lamb …

The roast chicken is a must-try! Very tasty. Everything I have had here so far has been nice and the price is reasonable.
Great chicken with nice service

A nice little, unpretentious restaurant with delicious food. The night we were there, a Saturday evening, there was only one main server, but he took his time to explain the menu and make recommendations. It was pretty amazing to see him in …
Our favorite restaurant in the city. I always get the lamb shank and my wife always gets the lomo saltado. Both are delicious.
Good food. Cramped space. That kind of adds to the charm though.
Nice staff, but the food wasn't that great, especially at that price

Coming from a Hispanic neighborhood on the East Coast and based on the reviews, I decided to try this place. The ceviche mixto wasn't tasty and the empanadas tasted like vinegar. Not the way food is suppossed to taste, and I'm thoroughly disappointed.
Latin American cuisine with a chic twist. Decent portions, great value, excellent service. Try to book in advance, the tiny place can get crowded!
Started with empanadas and yucca fries, which were excellent, but the seafood pot pie stole the show. Terrific sauce and good seafood ratio. Service was also great. Will definitely be back.
Better than many Valencia Street restaurants
Fantastic food. The empanadas, ceviche and banana empanadas for dessert was incredible.
Alright food, but expensive for the quantity. Right next to a cigar club, so don't sit by the door.

Great little place in under financial district serving mixed Latin cuisine. We had the mushroom strudel, roteserie chicken with a sober of tacu tacu and fondness with the banana empanadas. The food was lovely with beautiful presentation and friendly wait staff. Coming back here again soon.
Ceviche, seafood stew, and pork chop were all excellent.

We had their Empanadas (corn & fish), Yucca Fries, and Banana and Dulce de Leche Empanadas. I loved the sauces that came with the empanadas, it compliment together very well, my fave sauce was the piquillo pepper aioli. The Banana and Dulce …

Came here for another friend's birthday. We were in a group of 12 and just like the previous time, we end up being arranged around a pole. The pole essentially divides the table as this awkward divider. The seafood pot pie and truffle mac & …

Heard a lot of good things about the place but had a different experience myself. Booked the table for the group of ten and when arrived were told that the waiter just gave that table to another group assuming it was us. We had to look elsewhere... Not the best experience for a birthday lunch.
Great food. Try the Vodka drink options.

Small restaurant near Belden Alley. Friendly staff, a few interesting beer choices, but with very limited vegetarian options. Friends said their meat dishes were excellent, but vegetarians will assemble their dinner from appetizers, salads, …
Great service, delicious food with small portion sizes but so tasty! Must try dessert.
Got the Champinones Envueltos for takeaway. When I opened the box it seemed pretty small but it filled me up and was delicious. Will be back for sure!
My palate was challenged and satisfied
Cozy place, fast service, friendly staff and food is simply amazing.
The food was amazing and the servers were very attentive.  It is a small cozy restaurant that does not jave the typical hipster feel of San Francisco restaurants, and that's a good thing.
Best restaurant I have visited in SF ever! I ordered La Fusion seafood pot pie and 1/2 rotisserie chicken with sweet potato fries and both were awesome!! I'll try Tuna tartar next time!
Great experience here. Empanadas to start, rotiserie chicken with side of truffle mac and cheese as the main. All were delicious.
Service friendly, accommodated our finicky son with sauce on side, highly recommended!
very good for the price. empanada was stellar. really enjoyed both the chicken and the lomo saltado.
This place was so good. Recommended by the bell hop...amazing cerviche, everyone couldn't be nicer
Dinner here blew my mind. We ordered 1/2 rotisserie chicken with bread salad, truffle Mac and cheese and seafood pot pie. Every bite was amazing. I would highly recommend. We'll be back.

The food was really wonderful. The atmosphere was ok, it didn't quite match the food on offer. The service was friendly.  We shared:  1/2 Rotisserie Chicken with Bread Salad Truffled Mac and Cheese Romaine Salad Tres Leches de Maracuya  It …
Very good food and perfect service
Wonderful
I've been here many times for lunch and the rotisserie chicken with the sauces is the best. The chimichurri, in particular, is just amazing. I could eat that stuff by the bowl!

Absolutely delicious!  The set course for $35 is an amazing deal! Salad, empanadas, civiche, seafood pot pie, kobe beef w/ fries, and for dessert the empanada with banana amazing!  Also the staff is wonderful! Loved it!
The best Latin food I've had in San Francisco!
Really good food. The mac and cheese was gooey and super tasty. The chickan sandwich was large and really good. With your meal you get some sauces that really added to the meal.

Made it a date night with the bf and Thor and couldn't have been happier.  It's kind of tucked away between two different places, so you can almost miss it.  Small and modern inside with not that many tables, so make sure you call in for a …

Delicious delicious food. Ceviche was great, chicken delicious, sangria yum... Great restaurant
Such a great place. Excellent food and extraordinary service.

We went here for a friends birthday party.  With a total of 14 people, we had to be on the fixed menu.  The food was scrumptious and they even accommodated different diets (one vegetarian and one pescaterian).  Overall, a must try ;)

This place is quite hidden to a point of not having signage at the front...but if you are able to find it, it's a treasure hunt.  The empanadas are excellent along with the truffle-laced mac and cheese.  Great price as well!
The ceviche is mind-blowing with a very nice menu of different flavors to boot. My personal recommendation is their ahi tuna - mucho bueno!

Was not expecting anything spectacular but the food truly blew my mind away! Affordable, delicious and adventurous dishes, though all the best items are meat dishes so would not recommend for vegetarians.  Also the decor and ambiance is simple and functional so don't pick if you are looking for something fancier.

They happened to have a special tasting menu when we went there, but the waiters kept forgetting which items haven't been served yet. Food was decent but not overwhelming. Place is too small, especially with people standing near the bar.
Everything was stand out perfect.   Service,  staff and most exceptionally,  the food.
Nice interior.
